## Toast POS Integration — IN PROGRESS

### Auth model — important, different from Square/Lightspeed

Toast does not use a standard OAuth redirect flow for third-party apps.
There are four access tiers:

- **Partner integration** — formal Toast partnership; full read/write; proper OAuth; users connect via Toast Marketplace. Apply at https://doc.toasttab.com/doc/devguide/integrationDevProcess.html
- **Custom integration** — per-restaurant clientId/clientSecret issued in Toast developer portal. Credentials are per-location, not per user. Best for a single business's own dev team.
- **Standard API access** — self-service, purchased per location through Toast Shop. Read-only. Credentials created by the restaurant owner in Toast Web.
- **Analytics API access** — requires Toast Restaurant Management Suite Pro subscription. Read-only sales/labor/menu data. Credentials created in Toast Web.

**For Batch Maker:** We are a third-party app connecting multiple customers' Toast accounts.
The correct long-term path is a **partner integration**. The short-term unblocked path is
**custom integration** — each Batch Maker user who uses Toast generates their own
clientId + clientSecret + restaurantGuid in Toast Web and pastes them into Batch Maker.
This is the same pattern used by many smaller integrations before partner approval.

### Authentication flow
```
POST https://ws-api.toasttab.com/authentication/v1/authentication/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "clientId": "<clientId>",
  "clientSecret": "<clientSecret>",
  "userAccessType": "TOAST_MACHINE_CLIENT"
}
```
Returns `{ token: { tokenType, accessToken, expiresIn } }`.
Tokens are short-lived — refresh before each sync. All subsequent requests require:
```
Authorization: Bearer <accessToken>
Toast-Restaurant-External-ID: <restaurantGuid>
```

### Key sales endpoint
```
GET https://ws-api.toasttab.com/orders/v2/ordersBulk
    ?startDate=<ISO>&endDate=<ISO>
```

### Tasks
- [ ] Apply for Toast Partner Integration — https://doc.toasttab.com/doc/devguide/integrationDevProcess.html
- [ ] `pages/api/pos/toast-connect.ts` — accepts `clientId`, `clientSecret`, `restaurantGuid` from user; fetches token; encrypts + stores all three in `pos_connections`
- [ ] `pages/api/pos/toast-refresh.ts` — re-authenticates with stored credentials before expiry
- [ ] Update `POSConnectionCards.tsx` — Toast card shows a form for clientId / clientSecret / restaurantGuid with a link to the Toast Web guide
